The paper discusses the use of machine learning in the context of Radio Resource Management (RRM) in 5G networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also presents a learning framework for RRM, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG - Machine Learning) and information theory (cs.IT - Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of implementing this framework, which could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI - Artificial Intelligence) and systems and control (cs.SY - Systems and Control).
